<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="490" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1618,2041]" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,1618,1644]" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">Remarks.</emphasis>
Among the most important characters of this species are the presence of dense metatergal setation, and of adenostyles only on male femora 2, coupled with the gonofemorite being quite slender and long, but with clear evidence of torsion, while the solenophore is also peculiar in shape and rather similar to that of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Carl" baseAuthorityYear="1932" box="[1244,1407,1691,1716]" class="Diplopoda" family="Paradoxosomatidae" genus="Polydrepanum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="5" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asperrimum">
<emphasis box="[1244,1407,1691,1716]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">P. asperrimum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: a large, rounded, mesal lobe (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[464,495,1726,1752]" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">lo)</emphasis>
, but only a single apicolateral spine (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[916,930,1726,1752]" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">a</emphasis>
) distal to the basal loop of a free solenomere (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[161,180,1762,1788]" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">sl</emphasis>
). Base of 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[299,321,1762,1788]" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">lo</emphasis>
on mesal side forming a protecting shield for the basal 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[962,981,1762,1788]" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">sl</emphasis>
loop. Distal half of solenophore clearly curved and directed laterad (
<figureCitation box="[470,587,1798,1824]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–12" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1167,1191]" captionTargetBox="[164,1428,188,1137]" captionTargetId="figure-22@6.[151,1436,181,1143]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 9–12. Polydrepanum horridum Golovatch, 1984. Right gonopod, lateral, dorsal, mesal and ventral views, respectively.After Golovatch (1984). Abbreviations: a, apicolateral spine; k, basal loop of solenomere; lo, mesal lobe; sl, solenomere; sph, solenophore. Scale bar: 0.4 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5709518" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5709518/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">Figs 9–12</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1618,2041]" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">
Despite some critical comments following the original description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Golovatch" authorityYear="1984" box="[982,1116,1834,1860]" class="Diplopoda" family="Paradoxosomatidae" genus="Polydrepanum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="5" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="horridum">
<emphasis box="[982,1116,1834,1860]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">P. horridum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Bano, 1997, 1998; 
<bibRefCitation author="Bano, K. &amp; Murthy, J. B." pageId="5" pageNumber="490" pagination="155 - 162" refId="ref13259" refString="Bano, K. &amp; Murthy, J. B. (1997) Gonopods of some South Indian paradoxosomatid millipedes (Diplopoda, Polydesmida). Entomologica Scandinavica, Supplement 51, 155 - 162." type="journal article" year="1997">Bano &amp; Murthy, 1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Nguyen, A. D. &amp; Sierwald, P." box="[318,616,1870,1897]" pageId="5" pageNumber="490" pagination="1132 - 1353" refId="ref15022" refString="Nguyen, A. D. &amp; Sierwald, P. (2013) A worldwide catalog of the family Paradoxosomatidae Daday, 1889 (Diplopoda: Polydesmida). Check List, 9 (6), 1132 - 1353. [https: // www. researchgate. net / publication / 261875647 _ A _ worldwide _ catalog _ of _ the _ family _ Paradoxosomatidae _ Daday _ 1889 _ Diplopoda _ Polydesmida] https: // doi. org / 10.15560 / 9.6.1132" type="journal article" year="2013">Nguyen &amp; Sierwald, 2013</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Golovatch, S. I. &amp; Wesener, T." box="[628,947,1870,1897]" pageId="5" pageNumber="490" pagination="1" refId="ref14314" refString="Golovatch, S. I. &amp; Wesener, T. (2016) A species checklist of the millipedes (Myriapoda, Diplopoda) of India. Zootaxa, 4129 (1), 001 - 075. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4129.1.1" type="journal article" year="2016">Golovatch &amp; Wesener, 2016</bibRefCitation>
) that suggested the erection of a new genus to accommodate this species alone, we still feel that the distinctions are not strong enough to do so, because both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Golovatch" authorityYear="1984" class="Diplopoda" family="Paradoxosomatidae" genus="Polydrepanum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="5" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="horridum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">P. horridum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Carl" authorityYear="1932" box="[309,428,1942,1968]" class="Diplopoda" family="Paradoxosomatidae" genus="Polydrepanum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="5" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tamilum">
<emphasis box="[309,428,1942,1968]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">P. tamilum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(cf. 
<figureCitation box="[477,588,1942,1968]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–12" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1167,1191]" captionTargetBox="[164,1428,188,1137]" captionTargetId="figure-22@6.[151,1436,181,1143]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 9–12. Polydrepanum horridum Golovatch, 1984. Right gonopod, lateral, dorsal, mesal and ventral views, respectively.After Golovatch (1984). Abbreviations: a, apicolateral spine; k, basal loop of solenomere; lo, mesal lobe; sl, solenomere; sph, solenophore. Scale bar: 0.4 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5709518" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5709518/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">Figs 9–12</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[640,711,1942,1968]" captionStart="FIGURES 16–20" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1772,1796]" captionTargetBox="[155,1426,1008,1740]" captionTargetId="figure-321@8.[151,1437,1002,1749]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 16–20. Polydrepanum tamilum Carl, 1932. 16. Male leg 2, lateral view. 17. Entire left gonopod, mesal view. 18. Distal half of left gonopod, lateral view. 19. Entire right gonopod, mesal view. 20. Distal half of right gonopod, sublateral view. 16–18: after Carl (1932); 19, 20: after Jeekel (1980b). Abbreviations: a and b, dorsal distofemoral processes; ad, adenostyle; lo, lateral protecting lobe/shield; k, basal loop of solenomere; sl, solenomere; sph, solenophore. Drawn not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5709524" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5709524/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">17–19</figureCitation>
) share such decisive characters as a twisted gonofemorite and the basal loop of a flagelliform solenomere (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[610,629,1978,2004]" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">sl</emphasis>
) protected by a large lobe (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[939,970,1978,2004]" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">lo)</emphasis>
of a distally strongly curved solenophore (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[161,203,2014,2040]" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">sph</emphasis>
). In other words, we consider 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Golovatch" authorityYear="1984" box="[545,678,2014,2040]" class="Diplopoda" family="Paradoxosomatidae" genus="Polydrepanum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="5" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="horridum">
<emphasis box="[545,678,2014,2040]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">P. horridum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as being congeneric with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Carl" authorityYear="1932" box="[971,1091,2014,2040]" class="Diplopoda" family="Paradoxosomatidae" genus="Polydrepanum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polydesmida" pageId="5" pageNumber="490" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tamilum">
<emphasis box="[971,1091,2014,2040]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">P. tamilum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
